data.name: label70.Text
data.value:
Parsing Expressions are used by the plugins parsing engine to retrieve a Artist, Album and Track from a Folder Structure / Filename in your Import Paths. This information is required to successfully match up with the online database.
If an expression can not evaluate these items, the next expression in the list is used.

data.name: cbAlbumFromTrackData.ToolTip
data.value:
Enable album parsing support using the the folder structure as the primary method i.e
..\<artist>\<album>\<track>.<ext> or ..\<artist>\<album>\<artist - track>.<ext>
If no album is found the album will be retrived from Last.FM if possible. This method can produce some odd results as the primary album is not always the highest ranked
Default Setting: Enabled

data.name: cbPreferThumbnail.ToolTip
data.value:
Enabling this option will force the importer to grab the track thumbnail image from the Video being imported.
This uses MTN to grab the fram and muliple row/columns are supported.
Default Settings: Enabled

data.name: autoDataSourcesPanel1.ToolTip
data.value:
Select the language that Artist and track descriptions should be retrived.
The main languages supported by last.FM are listed, you can chose a langiage not support by Lat.FM and this will be run though Google Translate.
Default Setting: Language defined for MediaPortal.

data.name: cbEnableVideoStartInfo.ToolTip
data.value:
When enabled the skin property #mvCentral.Play.Starting will be set to true, this will allow supporting skins to display an info box with the main video details for a few seconds.
There is an assoiated timer that can be configured to reduce or extend the timeout (5 Secs by default)
Default Setting: Enabled

data.name: cbClearPlaylistOnAdd.ToolTip
data.value:
When queing a new playlist either via loading, smartplaylist or pressing play on an Artist, Album of Genre disabling this option will not clear the current playlist, if one exists.
This all allow the building of playlist from mulitple Artsts, Albums or Genres.
Default Setting : Enabled

data.name: cbGeneratedAutoShufflePlaylist.ToolTip
data.value:
Enabling this option will Shuffle all playlists generted by the pligin.
Internal playlist are those generated via Smart Playlists or by pressing play on Artists, Albums or Genres.
Default Setting: Enabled

data.name: cbDisplayRawTrackText.ToolTip
data.value:
Selecting this option will display the raw track name against the cleaned version.
i.e. for Track: ACDC - Highway to Hell (with Bon Scott).mpg
Raw Track Name: Highway to Hell (with Bon Scott) Cleaned Track Name: Highway to Hell
Default Setting: Disabled

data.name: cbAutoFullscreen.ToolTip
data.value:
This option keeps all videos in a playlist at fullscreen.
Disabling this option will drop back to the plugin or current screen and is usefull if you just want the music and a small video overlay.
Default Settings: Enabled

data.name: label25.Text
data.value: mvCentral is a plugin for the MediaPortal HTPC application. The purpose of the plugin is to catalog Music Videos and by looking up data from online sources create Music Video DB with Artwork and information about Artists, Albums and Tracks. Last.Fm is used as the primary datasource currently.
